    Score: 0,
    ViewCount: 59,
    Body: "<p>I have a problem with my Arducam OV5647 M32076M20. It simply will not work unlike the other generic rpi camera I have on the same code. I am unsure if there are any other dependencies that I need for this.</p>\n<p>Things to note:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><p><code>vcgencmd get_camera</code> returns <code>supported=1 detected=1, libcamera interfaces=0</code></p>\n</li>\n<li><p>I am using <code>OpenCV</code> and <code>tkinter</code> and its basically just a simple program that shows what the camera sees when its turned on. It works on other camera except the one I've shown</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>I have a script that detects camera with cv2 and it returns positive with <code>video0</code> usually</p>\n<pre><code> for i in range(10):\n     vid = cv2.VideoCapture(i)\n     if vid.isOpened():\n         status_label.config(text=&quot;Camera Found\\tPort: video&quot; + str(i), fg=&quot;green&quot;)\n         print(&quot;Camera Found port: &quot; + str(i))\n         break\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n<li><p>GPU Memory is at <code>256</code></p>\n</li>\n<li><p><code>libcamera-hello</code> runs and I see myself in the camera but I cannot get it to work in the software I coded</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>Legacy Camera is <code>enabled</code> in <code>raspi-config</code></p>\n</li>\n<li><p>Details of <code>cat /etc/os-release</code></p>\n<pre><code> PRETTY_NAME=&quot;Raspbian GNU/Linux 11 (bullseye)&quot;\n NAME=&quot;Raspbian GNU/Linux&quot;\n VERSION_ID=&quot;11&quot;\n VERSION=&quot;11 (bullseye)&quot;\n VERSION_CODENAME=bullseye\n ID=raspbian\n ID_LIKE=debian\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Really stumped at this. does Arducam have specific dependencies that I somehow missed. -I am just hoping that theres no need to buy the same module again to compare- <strong>Edit: Nope. Even with another module its still the same</strong></p>\n<p>Edit:\nI tried <code>dmesg</code> and saw these</p>\n<pre><code>    [ 1638.317199] unicam fe801000.csi: Failed to start media pipeline: -22\n    [ 1678.153954] unicam fe801000.csi: Wrong width or height 640x480 (remote pad set to 1296x972)\n</code></pre>\n<p>I am still trying to figure out what this means</p>\n<p>I get <code>global cap_v4l.cpp: 1119 tryIoctl VIDEOI0(V4L2:/dev/video0): select() timeout</code> now that i did a fresh install and everything.</p>\n",
