    Body: "<p>I have a Python program that utilizes threading to run multiple processes on a single webcam. The code works perfectly fine on my laptop, where it can run different processes simultaneously on one camera. However, when I try to run the same code on my Raspberry Pi 4, it does not work at all... I don't understand why it's not working.</p>\n<pre><code>import threading\nfrom Head import HeadTracking\nfrom Hand2 import HandTracking\nfrom Monitoring import video_stream\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    head_tracking = HeadTracking()\n    hand_tracking = HandTracking()\n    video_stream = video_stream\n\n    head_thread = threading.Thread(target=head_tracking.run)\n    hand_thread = threading.Thread(target=hand_tracking.run)\n    video_thread = threading.Thread(target=video_stream)\n\n    head_thread.start()\n    hand_thread.start()\n    video_thread.start()\n\n    head_thread.join()\n    hand_thread.join()\n    video_thread.join()\n</code></pre>\n",
